			<div class="row">		
				<div class="left-side">
		
		
			<h1 id="ticket-news-hd">USA Fans					</h1>
							
		
			<h1>USA Celebrity Fan Focus: John Green</h1>
			<div class="article-top">
			<div class="article-date">
									8th July 2014							</div>
			<div class="parent-section">USA Fans</div>
				<div class="article-social-sharing"> 
						<div class="social_facebook">
						<div id="fb-root"></div><script src="http://connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1"></script><fb:like href="http://www.lfctour.com/news/fan-news/usa-celebrity-fan-focus-john-green" send="true" show_faces="false" width="60" layout="button_count" font=""></fb:like>
						</div>
						<div class="social_google">
												<g:plusone href="http://www.lfctour.com/news/fan-news/usa-celebrity-fan-focus-john-green" count="false" size="medium"></g:plusone>
						</div>  
						<div class="social_twitter">
						<a href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-count="none" data-via="lfc">Tweet</a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script> 
						</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content article-body image-full-width">
				<p><strong>John Green is probably best known as an award-winning, bestselling novelist – author of ‘Looking for Alaska’, ‘An Abundance of Katherines’ and ‘The Fault in Our Stars’. </strong></p>
	
					
																				<img alt="" class="article-image" src="http://assets.lfcimages.com/uploads/1515__9686__johngreen.jpeg" />																		
				
				<div id="cmsContentId" class="cmsContent content-link-builder" ><p>Others may know him from his highly-popular video blogs on YouTube. However, what many of his fans probably don't know is that he's also a passionate supporter of Liverpool Football Club. LFCTour.com's Maria Xing caught up with him to discuss his love of the Reds...</p>
<p><strong>Name</strong>: John Green<br /><strong>Age</strong>: 36<br /><strong>City / State</strong>: Indianapolis, IN<br /><strong>Job</strong>: Novelist and Videoblogger.</p>
<p><strong>Why did you pick Liverpool as your team?</strong><br /> <br /> "To be honest, I don't even remember. I probably heard 'You'll Never Walk Alone' once on TV and got hooked. I've been following the club closely since 2001-2002."<br /> <br /><strong> Who was your first LFC hero and why?</strong> <br /> <br /> "Steven Gerrard, because he loves the club. I know our opponents sing about how he kissed the badge on his chest and then put in a transfer request, but look, he's a one-club man. He's been with us in the best times and the worst times. There are a lot of great players at Liverpool, but only once or twice in a generation do you have a one-club guy like Stevie. We've been lucky to have had Carra as well. The real legends stay, and then their names are sung for generations. Stevie stayed. It hasn't always been easy, but he has stayed."<br /> <br /><strong> What is your favourite LFC memory? </strong><br /> <br /> "Istanbul is my favorite memory on the pitch but my favorite memory came on September 12, 2012 when at long last the Hillsborough Independent Panel published its findings. It was a huge step to see he truth finally come out and be published in every paper in the UK."<br /> <br /><strong> Who has been your favourite Liverpool manager and why? </strong><br /> <br /> "Probably Rafa. I love Brendan Rodgers, and I love Kenny, and I'm so grateful to Kenny for coming in and bringing stability to the club when we desperately needed it. But the crazy Champions League runs under Rafa were just so special to me. That said, I love the kind of football we're playing under Rodgers and I'm hopeful that he'll be the manager for decades."</p>
<p><img src="http://assets1.lfcimages.com/uploads/9790__0392__johngreen3.jpeg" alt="" width="1000" height="600" /></p>
<p><strong>Have you ever been to Anfield?</strong> <br /> <br /> "No! I have seen Liverpool games in the U.S. and England, but never at Anfield. I'm hoping to get there this season."<br /> <br /><strong> Where were you while we were in Istanbul? </strong><br /> <br /> "It was the day before my engagement party, so Sarah (my fiancee at the time; now wife) and I were at her parents' house doing wedding planning and whatnot. I almost stopped watching at halftime because I was so distraught, but then...'In towards Gerrard... HELLO! HELLO. Here we go....'"<br /> <br /><strong> Do Liverpool have a passionate fan base in your state? </strong><br /> <br /> "Yes, there's a nice collection of Liverpool supporters in Indianapolis who meet every week for the games at a pub. I usually do not attend because I like to watch with my 4-year-old son."<br /> <br /><strong> Which team is to be considered Liverpool's biggest rival in America? </strong><br /> <br /> "Manchester United. There are a lot of Arsenal fans in the US so I think American Liverpool fans view Arsenal even less charitably than English Reds. But yeah, United. The rivalry with Everton is less intense here than it is in Liverpool."</p>
<p><img src="http://assets1.lfcimages.com/uploads/9286__6763__johngreen2.jpeg" alt="" width="1000" height="1399" /></p>
<p><strong>Do you also support a local team? </strong><br /> <br /> "Yes, my local team is the Indy 11."<br /> <br /><strong> Who is your favourite current player and why? </strong><br /> <br /> "Gerrard is still my favorite player and will be as long as he plays. I admire his intensity, his commitment, and his ability to change his game as he ages. What I love most about football is unexpected beauty. Sometimes, a ball is played that opens up space in a way that I never could've imagined and the whole shape of the game changes. And in Liverpool's case, such balls are usually from the foot of Steven Gerrard."<br /> <br /><strong> If you could meet anyone connected to Liverpool FC - past or present - who would it be and why?</strong> <br /> <br /> "Oh, I'd want to meet Shankly. He seems like he'd be a hell of a good dinner guest."<br /> <br /><strong> What makes you most proud to be a Liverpool supporter? </strong><br /> <br /> "The idea that as a supporter of the club, or a player, or a friend, you will truly never walk alone."<br /> <br /><strong> Finally, what does 'the Liverpool way' mean to you? </strong><br /> <br /> "For me, it means that no one is bigger than the club and to take pride in the crest whether you are wearing it on the pitch, in the stands, or at home."</p>
<p>Click here to follow <a href="https://twitter.com/sportswithjohn" target="_blank"><strong>@sportswithjohn</strong></a>&nbsp;and <strong><a href="https://twitter.com/realjohngreen" target="_blank">@realjohngreen</a> </strong>on Twitter or <strong><a href="http://johngreenbooks.com/" target="_blank">click here to </a><a href="http://johngreenbooks.com/" target="_blank">visit his official website&gt;&gt;&nbsp;</a></strong><br /> <br /><strong><a href="http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/bos/ticketing/footballatfenway.jsp" target="_blank"> Liverpool's first match of the summer tour of America will take place on July 23<sup>rd</sup> against AS Roma at Fenway Park. Click here to buy tickets&gt;&gt;</a></strong></p></div>	
			</div>	

			<div class="article-bottom">
